"&#xa0;\nOAR0009Written evidence submitted by the CBI Submission&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;&#xa0;We need a clear statement of what it is we are asking schools to deliver. This should then form the basis of how schools are judged and held accountable by Ofsted.&#xa0;&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nStrong leadership and governance are key to ensuring successful education outcomes for young people, and Ofsted should continue to focus more acutely on this.&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nJanuary 2014\n&#xa0;\n \nLeading the way: improving school governance and leadership\n, CBI, November 2013\n \nThe Annual Report of Her Majesty’s Chief Inspector of Education, Children’s Services and Skills\n, Ofsted, December 2013\n Ibid.\n"